# cargo-fuzz outputs — never commit these.
target/
artifacts/
Cargo.lock

# `corpus/` holds two kinds of files:
#   1. Hand-curated seed inputs we ship (committed; small; one per
#      target; covers the happy-path shape so libFuzzer doesn't have
#      to reinvent it from random bytes).
#   2. libFuzzer-grown corpora from local runs (NOT committed; can
#      balloon to GBs; not deterministic across hosts).
#
# We ignore the directory by default, then `git add -f` each seed by
# name when seeding. New seeds added later need the same `-f` so
# they don't silently grow the repo.
corpus/
